hopobject.body: International directory enquiries viagra for sale online uk According to Tom Wagner, manager of the Cryosphere program at NASA, "Polar regions tend to heat up faster than the rest of the planet." Another part of the problem is that, according to Wagner, "The Arctic also has massive stores of methane in the permafrost and sea bed. As we lose the sea ice, we have more heat going into the ocean, causing more permafrost to die, which can destabilize the sea bed and trip the release of this methane, which could cause spikes in temperature." Methane is one of the most harmful greenhouse gasses - more harmful per volume than Carbon Dioxide.
